textDelta: electron distribution, dipole moment, force constant, reduced mass. Infrared absorption frequency of deuterium chloride is shifted from that of hydrogen chloride is due to which one? The deuterium chloride molecule has a higher dipole moment than the hydrogen chloride molecule. This leads to a stronger interaction between the electric fields of the molecules, and hence a higher infrared absorption frequency.

Infrared absorption frequency of deuterium chloride is shifted from that of hydrogen chloride is due to which one? The difference in the infrared absorption frequency of deuterium chloride and hydrogen chloride is due to the difference in the masses of the two atoms. Deuterium has a mass that is twice that of hydrogen, so its absorption frequency is shifted from that of hydrogen by a factor of 2.
